
[1]beef

   BEEF, n. [L. bos,bovis; Gr.Bous.]

   1. An animal of the bovine genus,whether ox, bull or cow; but used of
   those which are full grown or nearly so. In this, which is the original
   sense, the word has a plural, beeves.

   2. The flesh of an ox, bull, or cow, when killed. In popular language,
   the word is often applied to the live animal; as, an ox is good beef;
   that is,is well fattened. In this sense,the word has no plural.

      BEEF, a. Consisting of the flesh of the ox, or bovine kind; as a
                                 beef-steak.
